x10.mongo.yak
Class LoadedYakMap

x10.mongo.yak.LoadedYakMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
x10.lang.Any
public struct class LoadedYakMap
implements x10.lang.Any, x10.lang.Any

An auxiliary type, designed to have the y-<"a">-n idiom work.

This type provides the >- part of the idiom. It also has a few extra operations. Internally, it has properties yakMap:YakMap and newIndex:String. The interesting operations will modify yakMap.

Adds a new entry to yakMap at newIndex.
The basic idiom is, ym -< "a" >- 1  to add a new entry
at index "a" of YakMap ym having value 1.
